#1 Stage IIA (T3N0M0) adenocarcinoma of the colon status-post right hemicolectomy
#2 Multifactorial dementia, including Alzheimer's and multi-infarct dementia
#3 Multiple medical comorbidities
Mrs. Prime is a very pleasant 84-year-old female with recently resected stage IIA colon cancer.  We spent a fair amount of time speaking with her and her son in regard to her diagnosis and our treatment recommendations at this time.  The patient was very sleepy, however, and most of the information was relayed to her son.  The first goal of care for her will be for her to recover from the surgery.  We would then like to see her back in clinic in about four to six-weeks' time.  More than likely, we will not recommend any chemotherapy treatment options for her, due to the stage and features of her resected disease and also for her current performance status.  However, we will fully address this issue when she comes back for follow-up.  She is from KS and will likely continue follow-up from that point forward back near home, but this will be decided when she returns to the GI Clinic in about a month.  We answered all the patient's and her son's questions to the best of our ability.
Thank-you for allowing us to consult in Mrs. Prime's care.  Please do not hesitate to call us with any questions; our pager is 743-97700.

